to the editor re out of the mainstream again editorial oct 25 i do n't think our founding fathers ever imagined that a president would callously try to destroy their carefully developed system of checks and balances judicial appointments were to be for life so that decisions could be made fairly and judiciously without political consequences certainly there is room for different interpretations of the laws but impartiality was definitely the sine qua non where are we now president bush nominates judges with a preconceived agenda partial to the extreme and when the minority democrats try to prevent such appointments they are castigated and accused of political partisanship if we end up with one party and one extreme philosophy controlling the presidency both houses of congress and all newly appointed judges we will not only not have a system of checks and balances we will have a terrible rent in the increasingly stretched fabric of our democratic functioning ruth karter great neck ny oct 27 2003

